# Problem 1

## a)
Proof:

> $a \geq 0$ and arbitrary $b \in \mathbb{N}$

> $0 \in \mathbb{N}$, so $a \in \mathbb{N}$

> By definition of natural numbers, $0$ is the smallest natural number. Thus $0$ is the smallest natural number. Thus $a \geq b$ when $a = 0$, satisfying the condition $\square$

## b)
$x^2 - 2x - 8 = 0, (x-4)(x+2) = 0, x = 4, -2$

Roots of Quadratic Equation: $4, -2$
